{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Plum Sauce","content":["Place plums in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>15 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add garlic, soy sauce, sugar, tangerine peel, salt, ginger and water then chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then cook <nobr>20 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add cornflour mixture and mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer to an airtight container and store in fridge until cooled. Clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Prawn Patties","content":["Place prawns, pork, egg, sugar, sesame oil and pepper in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then chop again <nobr>5 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl.","Place a plate on mixing bowl lid, weigh on flour then remove plate. With wet hands, take 2 Tbsp prawn paste and shape into a ball. Coat with flour and flatten lightly into a patty. Place on a plate and dust with extra flour. Repeat until all mixture has been used (approx. 20 patties). Place in fridge for approx. 30 minutes.","Heat vegetable oil in a frying pan over a medium heat, shallow fry patties for 5 minutes, turning halfway through, until golden brown. Transfer to paper towels to drain excess oil then serve warm with plum sauce."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Plum Sauce","content":["100 g dried candied plums, pitted","5 garlic cloves","2 tsp soy sauce","2 Tbsp sugar","1 piece tangerine peel (1 cm x 4 cm),  soaked until soft then chopped","¼ tsp fine sea salt","10 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","300 g water","1 tsp cornflour, mixed with 1 Tbsp water"]},{"title":"Prawn Patties","content":["600 g raw prawns, peeled, deveined","70 g pork mince, broken in pieces","1 medium egg","1 tsp sugar","1 tsp sesame oil","2 pinches ground black pepper","120 g strong white bread flour, plus extra for dusting","vegetable oil, for frying"]}],"id":"r351515","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-KypppXVi3KM\/XZQxXTCWbnI\/AAAAAAAAcuY\/UrdqqE_3TFY4Ie2nw-7PP2-41PF7lBdBQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_q7uy6MxS7UBPsE-I.png","title":"Thai Prawn Patties","publishedAt":"2018-09-10T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6 g","fat":"2 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"5 g","calories":"233 kJ \/ 55 kcal"},"usefulItems":"airtight container, frying pan, paper towels, refrigerator, hob","hintsAndTricks":["These prawn patties are a perfect snack served with a cold drink such as lychee juice.","The plum sauce may be prepared in advance. It can be stored in the fridge for approx. <nobr>7-10 days<\/nobr> in an airtight container. This sauce goes well with seafood or white meat."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 20m","20 pieces"]}